post_text:
We are excited to announce that Woodland R-IV School District is now able to accept electronic payments for student meals. This option can be utilized by logging onto the parent portal https://sdm.sisk12.com/WO360x3/parent and clicking on the meal service balance then selecting the pay button. Step-by-step directions on how to set up and use the electronic meal payment option can be found at https://5il.co/kyhq .

Please keep in mind that all students are currently receiving free breakfast and lunch through December 31, 2020, so please add funds to meal accounts accordingly.

Woodland Community. Due to a reported case of COVID-19 on campus, we are using tomorrow, Tuesday 9/1, as an Alternative Method of Instruction (AMI) day to allow for accurate contact tracing and deep cleaning. All direct contacts will be notified immediately by a Woodland representative and/or the MO health department. Classes will resume Wednesday in Phase 3. Remember that Phase 3 requires masks be worn on the bus, while passing in the hallway, and a reminder that temps will be taken daily.

Information on the COVID-19 Opening of School Plan.
https://www.wsdr4.net/article/282181

post_text: Carly Harris, a fifth grade student at Woodland Middle School, placed first in Missouri with her essay for the Investwrite Competition. Carly worked after school with her teachers to create an essay about her choices in the Stock Market Game. She titled her essay, "Save more. Live Better." One of her choices in stocks was, you guessed it, Walmart! Carley received a medal, certificate, and $100. The Cardinals are proud of you Carly!

Woodland Jazz Band, FEB 8:
"A great day for jazz! We had a wonderful time at the PMA/Clark Terry Jazz Festival and learned so much from the fantastic clinicians and judges who worked with us. So proud of these young musicians, their progress this year, and their love of music!
If anyone is wondering if we ‚Äúwon‚Äù or what we scored, they don‚Äôt do that at many jazz festivals anymore. They focus on the music and helping them get better with clinics and classes instead. It provides a much more enriching experience for all." Mrs. Boyd #WHSJazzBand
NEXT EVENT - JACKSON JAZZ FESTIVAL FEB 29, 2020!
